import{_ as t,c as a,b as o,o as n}from"./chunks/framework.Bh4f_7Kc.js";const f=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"guide/Maslow.md","filePath":"guide/Maslow.md"}'),i={name:"guide/Maslow.md"};function s(r,e,l,h,p,d){return n(),a("div",null,e[0]||(e[0]=[o("<p>If your heart changes, your attitude will change tenfold; if your attitude changes, your habits will change tenfold; if your habits change, your character will change tenfold; if your character changes, your life will change tenfold.</p><p>---002---</p><p>Growing up is a painful process, but some people will force you to avoid growing up.</p><p>---003---</p><p>In order to avoid despairing of human nature, we must first abandon our illusions about human nature.</p><p>---004---</p><p>&quot;The hierarchy of human needs&quot;: the lowest level is the need for survival; second, the need for safety, stability and quality; third, the need for a sense of belonging; fourth, the need for respect; fifth, human needs for self and fulfillment.</p><p>---005---</p><p>If your only tool is a hammer, you might think all the problems are nails.</p><p>---006---</p><p>If you deliberately avoid the big things, and try your best to see the smaller things in your world, don&#39;t stand up, I warn you, in your big days, you are also making others unfortunate. Don&#39;t let me tell you that you are just trying to avoid the big things, but stand up for the various opportunities and possibilities that you can see in your world.</p><p>---007---</p><p>A musician must make music, an artist must paint, a poet must write, if he is to be ultimately at peace with himself. What a man can be, he must be.</p><p>A musician must compose music, a painter must paint, a poet must write poetry, and only in this way can one finally find the way. A person can be what he or she wants to be, and only in this way can one finally find the way to success.</p><p>---008---</p><p>Human beings have a great affinity with animals and have the ability to develop their own character. After studying the world for a long time, we can no longer see the world as it is.</p><p>---009---</p><p>When children feel insecure, when their needs for safety, love, belonging and self-esteem are fundamentally blocked and threatened, they will be more selfish, hateful, aggressive and destructive.</p><p>---010---</p><p>Compared to that, there is no need for us to think that such a great thing can be allowed to happen naturally. It just needs to keep its original state and not develop at will.</p><p>---011---</p><p>Not only do we love our best machines, but we also fear them.</p><p>---012---</p><p>A sense of honor and achievement is not a person&#39;s level of need to stand up to the great</p><p>---013---</p><p>It also requires thinking that the greater the level of calling, the more satisfactory the viewing experience, that is, a deeper sense of well-being, tranquility, and a real sense of richness in life.</p><p>---014---</p><p>An adult whose needs for love are met early in life is more likely to be alone and independent after a period of security, belonging, and love. It is these strong, healthy, self-aware people who are best able to withstand the loss of love and despair.</p><p>---015---</p><p>To the man who only has a hammer, everything he encounters begins to look like a nail.</p><p>To a person with only a hammer, the path he encounters only comes from this feeling and the heart does not look like a nail.</p><p>---016---</p><p>The most beautiful destiny and the most wonderful fate of mankind will open up, and at the same time, we will all be rewarded for our good fortune.</p><p>---017---</p><p>When people&#39;s basic needs are met, you will no longer have the need for respect and the need for love.</p><p>---018---</p><p>Man is an animal with constant needs. Except for a short period of time, he is rarely completely satisfied. One desire is quickly satisfied and another desire will occupy him. Man is almost always looking for something, which is the key point throughout his life.</p><p>---019---</p><p>Your attitude will change; if your attitude changes, your habits will change within ten times; if your habits change, your character will change within ten times; if your character changes, your life will change within ten times.</p><p>---020---</p><p>Creativity is a kind of ability that a person can develop after birth. It is a corrupt concept to limit creativity to the prolific creation of scientists, writers and artists. ... Creativity is a natural potential that a person can have as a member of the human race after birth. It is closely related to the healthy development of the mind. Under the condition of healthy development of the mind, everyone can show creativity.</p><p>---021---</p><p>If your hand is like a hammer, then your heart won&#39;t look like a nail.</p><p>---022---</p><p>Perfect love is marked by selflessness.</p><p>---023---</p><p>In any given moment we have two options: to step forward into growth or back into safety.</p><p>---024---</p><p>This is a course that helps to cultivate creativity. What we are saying is that educating people in a moral way helps to create a better type of person, which only makes you more creative in all aspects of your life.</p><p>---025---</p><p>We certainly admire those who embody the virtues of learning, kindness, beauty, justice and perfection, but in reality they also make us feel uneasy, anxious and confused, and perhaps a little jealous and envious, a little inferior and ashamed. This is what we call great people: just because of their presence and their greatness, they are enough to make us realize our own insignificance, regardless of whether they intend to do so or not.</p><p>---026---</p><p>We can fully understand this by assuming that people have an inherent or innate tendency to bring this tendency together in novels and the growth of small things.</p><p>---027---</p><p>Motivation and personality</p><p>---028---</p><p>When all you have is a hammer, every problem looks like a nail.</p><p>---029---</p><p>The theory of Dudilo&#39;s hierarchy of needs</p><p>Duddy&#39;s Hierarchy of Needs theory is the first theory to be proposed by American psychologist Albert Duddy in his paper &quot;A Theory of Human Motivation&quot; in 1943. The book also divides human needs into five levels, namely: survival needs, safety needs, social needs, esteem needs and self-performance needs.</p>",60)]))}const c=t(i,[["render",s]]);export{f as __pageData,c as default};
